headline: Gemini Stock Plunges After Earnings. Bitcoin Credit Cards Are Still Going Strong.
summary: Gemini Space Station  the cryptocurrency firm run by Cameron and Tyler Winklevoss of early  Facebook  fame, continues to fall out of orbit after its initial public offering.  Shares tumbled nearly 15% Tuesday—and hit their lowest level since September’s IPO—after Gemini reported a third-quarter net loss of $159.5 million, or $6.67 per share.  Gemini is investing heavily in its credit card business, which offers users rewards in numerous top cryptocurrencies, including Bitcoin, XRP, and Solana.

headline: Nebius’s 355% Revenue Hike Misses Forecasts. This AI Deal Isn’t Enough to Lift the Stock.
summary: Nebius  has become the latest artificial-intelligence infrastructure player to land a deal with a Mag 7 technology giant.  The Amsterdam-based company said Monday that it had signed a five-year agreement to deliver AI infrastructure to Meta Platforms, valued at roughly $3 billion.  While the company reported revenue of $146.1 million, a 355% increase from the prior year, this missed the $155.1 million consensus estimate among analysts polled by FactSet.
